      "span_text": "To date nearly 40 mutations associated with FTDP-17T or related disorders have been identi�ed (reviewed in ) (Figure 4). ese are all either missense mutations, mutations that affect splicing, or both, and almost all cluster in the portion encoding the C-terminal region or in an intervening sequence near exon 10. e C-terminal missense mutations all appear to impair tau binding to microtubules and the ability of tau to promote microtubule assembly, while a disease-associated mutation of a conserved arginine in the N-terminal region has been found to disrupt binding to the p150 subunit of the dynactin complex"
